Iranian students are ready to die for their country's core program.
They formed a living shield.
Several hundred university students formed a living shield around a core object in Iran.
With this gesture, they wanted to demonstrate their support for their country's core program before a possible Israeli attack.
The students had prayed in front of the object Tuesday noon and then announced death to the US and Israel.
On Tuesday, a few hundred students from the University of Isfahan, Iran, formed a living shield around the nuclear technology center in Isfahan, where uranium is processed.
They wanted to show that they are willing to protect their country's core programme, if necessary with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) recently stated in its report that Iran seems to have long since abandoned its efforts to create a nuclear weapon.
In Israel, too, there is talk of a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
Students had prayed at noon in front of the entrance to the complex and then announced death to the United States and Israel.
