The menu of a fat addicted child: It does not eat breakfast and eats sausage for dinner
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 have problems with overweight, with 9 percent of all students and 5 percent of all children being overweight.
Recent surveys have proven that obese children mostly come from families with unhealthy lifestyles.
This shows once again how important for the healthy development of a human being is the environment in which he grows up and is the examples that surround him.
On the tables of obese children, sausages are up to half more frequently on the table than in families where normal - weight children live.
More than 19 percent of overweight children had fries for dinner on the eve of the educational campaign under the motto "Adiposita is no coincidence".
In families with fat children, sport is not exactly one of the favourite activities, however, as the majority of today's students do - only 15 percent replied that their parents find time for active exercise at least once a week.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place last year towards the end of the school year, with almost 900 children from primary schools throughout the Czech Republic being interviewed.
This was already the second year of the action "Adiposita is not a coincidence", which is supported by the general health insurance company and Unilever.
To date, more than 12 thousand pupils from 4th and 8th classes have participated in the project.
Unhealthy diet and lack of exercise in the family are key factors that are responsible for the alarmingly rising number of children who are overweight or even obese.
"Only half of the children surveyed mentioned, for example, five times a day, eating breakfast-second breakfast-lunch-vesper dinner in the mode - one of the main prerequisites for a healthy diet," says one of the survey results.
No breakfast and sausage for dinner
Experts point out that relative small things, such as the regular breakfast time of the family, are also important for the healthy development of a child.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23 percent of the pupils' families have breakfast.
And - in most families everyone eats breakfast alone.
The worst was the finding that one in ten families is not having breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the cornerstone of a healthy daily diet.
The survey test revealed, among other things, that unhealthy fries are consumed much more often in the families of overweight children.
And almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet lemonades every day (70 percent)
Although more than 40 percent of the children surveyed are doing sports, only less than half of their parents do so - only 15 percent.
Configure your own menu
Another part of the survey made it possible for selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to compile their own menu from the options offered for appetite and opinion.
"What Czech children between 12 and 15 prefer in terms of nutrition is far from the ideal of a healthy diet.
Among her favorite dishes were many flour dishes, meat dishes and, of course, sweets.
"Alarming is above all the great popularity of sweet lemonades", is emphasized in the final report to this survey.
At lunch, i.e. the main dish, pasta won just before poultry.
The children almost didn't like legumes at all and the popularity of fish and vegetable dishes as lunch was also very low.
Return to Health
At the same time, the survey also showed that children are quite willing to change their eating habits when they get the right information.
"In many cases, the survey participants' control group, which completed the questionnaire after the explanatory presentation "Adiposity is not a coincidence", showed a significant shift in preferences towards principles of healthy nutrition", is mentioned in the results of the project.
This was obvious, for example, in the sweet limos, where many children began to give priority to ordinary water.
The children also crossed poultry or fish much more often in the questionnaire than the main dish of the day and were ready to eat less dumplings or sweet food.
Pros claim - a stylist must also be a good psychologist
In the introductory article about how stylists learn, I had managed to learn a little bit that this was a bit too much stuff for the beginning.
I had no idea what was coming.
Lectures by three professionals from the industry, the clothing of problematic figures and a seminar about how the "on the square" is going.
It's supposed to get worse.
The closer the examination comes, the more information and practical tasks are ahead of us.
But even if the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, it is still fully occupied.
This time we discussed with director Alena (not a single man participates in the course) how to put on a woman who does not have an ideally proportioned figure.
And that's what most of us are.
Some have one too short neck, the others a too young figure without proper curves and yet others are chubby.
It is up to the stylist to optically conceal broad shoulders, to lengthen the neck or to conjure up the necessary curves.
We also got tips on how to put on a female type like Jennifer Lopez - that is, with a big bosom, a wide hip and a narrow waist - pretty and figure-emphasized, without her being too provocative.
For example, if the difference between waist and hips is so big that the skirt or pants really don't fit, you should at least have a piece of custom cut.
Surely you will not regret this, because well - seated clothing is simply priceless.
In such a tailor-made skirt you feel much better than in one of the bars that always slips up and down, stands down in the waist, etc.
Young figures can, in turn, allow themselves to wear clothing with wrinkles, building blocks, applications, embroidery or raffling.
With this amount of information and figure types, I am glad that I have a whole week to let everything go through my head thoroughly.
And yet, I'm afraid that given the homework I'm assigned, it's almost impossible to do it.
Each of the students was assigned a celebrity for whom she is supposed to think up suitable outfits - day clothes and evening robes.
Here we should take into account the current appearance, the fashion style of the corresponding star and its figure type.
I'm supposed to "dress" Miranda Kerr, who you may know from the Victoria's Secret campaign.
On the inside I juble, because this is much better for me personally than for example to attract Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who has probably increased to a hundred kilos in recent times (well, that's a bit exaggerated), or also the young Selena Gomez.
We are supposed to cut the garments out of magazines or search the internet, print them out, and then print them out.
In the "Moodboard", as the whole result is called, our very personal style and our relationship to graphic design should then be expressed.
It is very important to also think about the graphic side of styling.
The stylist not only attracts the models physically, but also designs the so-called product page in the journals (according to concrete specifications, for example trend handbags, coats, etc.).
The stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about this.
But that's not until Sunday.
This means that a stylist must have a good overall view.
The Saturday lecture filled with information about character types was equally seasoned by three visitors from the industry:
by stylist Jan Pokorný, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is illusion and that a stylist should be able to exploit it.
And a stylist can work with a single piece of clothing in quite different ways.
The magic word is variability.
For example, you can wear a trench coat over the jeans as usual, like a T-shirt or coat, but you can also wear it on the naked body, put on heel shoes and wear it as a dress.
It's enough to roll up the sleeves or collar and the whole look looks completely different.
"Play with it," he stressed.
The most important advice, however, was the following: "First, you must know the rules perfectly."
"Only then can you hurt her," said Jakub.
Finally, I realize why we have to poke all these phrases, what can be combined with what, and why, even if you often get to see very different things in fashion journals.
Not to mention fashion shows.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I now know that a stylist must have prepared a lot more clothing variants than he finally photographed.
So for a fashion story with ten pages (i.e. ten outfits) you have to be prepared to style at least fifteen.
And also that the clothing on the photo in combination with other accessories sometimes looks completely different than in reality.
So you have to count on all this when designing the outfit.
Jan Pokorný also confirmed that image and style sometimes account for half of the success.
You just need to look at Madonna, a not exactly brilliant singer, from whom image and marketing have made a world star.
In the Czech Republic, the services of a stylist are rather reserved.
Also well-known personalities often consider this to be thrown out money (the main thing is that I bring something that I look like is secondary).
And if any of us can be styled, then we should expect that he or she will most likely force us to have a completely different (smaller) size than he or she really needs.
Then you only need to google afterwards, in order to determine with certainty that the tabloid press writes that the corresponding celebrity has returned to or lost, etc.
On Sunday, Jan and Mario told us not to believe that a stylist only needs to focus on fashion and then "to assemble" the outfit.
In his work, he has to communicate with the people he styles, and he has to be a smart psychologist.
Appreciate people without bowing down and agreeing to their opinions.
"If any manager orders us to look at her wardrobe and add nice pieces, then we can't clean out the whole closet and tell her - my God, that's terrible."
"You have to find at least a few praiseworthy things to which you recommend what you can carry," says Mario.
He also showed us in concrete terms what a so-called "space bag" must contain.
So it's a bag that you button at the waist and carry with you all the necessary proprieties.
Apart from such clear things as scissors, scrapers for removing hair or safety pins, it also contains such utensils as a nylon thread (which helps the stylist to photograph products, such as handbags or hats), special clips that are used to pick up the clothing at the back if it is too large (plug pins or other clamps are prohibited so that the fabric does not break) and of course sewing gear.
But so that we not only have to listen, but can also try something practical, we learned how to stick shoes properly.
Also when photographing in the studio, where the floor is flat, you can damage the shoe sole, let alone the outside.
We were stuck and glued...
With scissors, you can't even touch the shoes so you don't damage them.
So you really have to proceed skillfully.
Mario pleased me by praising my "creation" without restrictions.
The skill mentioned is not exactly my strength.
All this was only a fraction of what we heard at the second weekend course.
One thing has now become clear to me - to devote oneself to styling at a professional level is not a breeze.
V Need for Speed: "The Run" - the illegal race across America
Review
The originally carefree ride is due to a series of completely avoidable, dilettantic mistakes to the routine ride to the early shift.
Although it succeeded in fulfilling the ambitions to a large extent, what good is it if obviously no one wanted to do a little more.
Even before he got on the counters, the new part with the subtitle "The Run" aroused high expectations.
He promised to move the old-fashioned game series "Need for Speed" back into a new dimension and in the playable demonstration examples he did not seem to be just one of many action racing games.
We were also curious about the fitting passages in which the main protagonist gets out of the car and continues on foot.
But as you are already used to with NFS, in the end, much is different than you had expected.
Sure - potentially it's quite decent arcade races, but overall, the game is reduced by some superfluous mistakes that have more or less been present in this series for a few years.
So it's actually no longer a mistake, but rather a sign of in principle incomprehensible laziness of game developers.
The adventure starts very well.
First, one is introduced to history, whose main character Jack has certain problems of personal character; the only solution seems to be to participate in an illegal race across America.
In San Francisco, on the west coast, you sit on the wheel - with the task of being the first in New York.
The basic idea includes a whole series of interesting elements.
The entire route is divided into ten stages and more than fifty individual races.
This means that each race takes place on a different course and that the individual stages take place in different, sufficiently different and interesting environments.
You don't have a moment the impression that game would always offer the same thing.
Some environments are also very nice to look at, although the technical level of the graphics does not go beyond that of the earlier parts of the series.
So nothing world-moving.
But the ride through the desert, through autumnal landscape or high up through deep snowy landscape is visually very pleasant.
Every now and then, untypical elements bring a little variety into the individual races.
In the desert, for example, one is surprised by a desert storm that severely restricts visibility.
In the mountains, on the other hand, you have to be very careful not to be spilled by an avalanche.
By the way, the individual races are installed quite well in a row.
Only a few, but they're enough.
For a while you try to overtake the prescribed number of opponents (in principle a classic race), then you have time to catch up (classic race against the stopwatch), then you expect a personal duel with a single opponent.
And that's what the police are doing, trying to screw up the whole thing.
A novelty are passages in which Jack leaves the car.
It's more about certain interactive animations in which Jack escapes from someone and where the player has to help him by pressing the right button at the right moment.
So nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are much less such passages in the game than one would expect (in fact, only three).
Ultimately, this is more to the advantage of the thing, because this element has at least no chance of becoming boring - it is one of the elements that makes the game more varied in the context of what is said above.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of the previous parts.
This means, as seen from today’s point of view, it does not rip out trees, but on the other hand it cannot be said that it is bad.
If you are looking for realistic simulations, you have to look elsewhere.
But the local driving model continues to do quite well for action-packed racing, although you could find better in the competition.
Until then, everything is in order.
Real problems only appear after some time.
In contrast to the driving model, the collision model is not quite OK.
From a game of this kind it is hardly to be expected that it calculates complicated deformations and collisions, but if you have practically no idea before any impact on any object how the car behaves, then obviously not everything is fine.
Typical example: When you overtake or drive by oncoming cars, you "strip" the other cars in some places, but in other, almost identical situations you get into the sling and turn wild pirouettes.
Or the car's going to wreck.
Thanks to the restart system, it doesn't matter, it's always annoying.
The restarts are solved like this: if you have total damage or if you land far away from the track, the game throws you back to the last clue of the track.
Only - in every race you only have five restarts.
Once you've exhausted them, everything starts from the beginning.
So the restarts are more like a tool, in case something doesn't succeed, but you shouldn't rely on it.
Sometimes, however, the rest does not help, since nothing else helps to learn the critical section from the head.
Very unpleasant is that the same things often happen in the same places.
Some curves, for example, you have to go through in a very specific way, otherwise you just don't fit through.
Elsewhere, you always meet "civil" cars in the appropriate place in the same configuration, whether you are the first or fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is particularly annoying in situations where you can see that the opponent passes two oncoming cars in front of a player, but until you get there yourself, the cars are already in such a position that you have to drive them around or brake them.
And it doesn't matter when you get there, because everything is designed in such a way that this situation always comes close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
In the whole game there are a few places where you will always be overtaken in the same place by the same opponent and here again without regard to the time.
The craziest thing to do is to finish the game on the long bridge that you pass in opposite direction.
The opponent obviously has to overtake you here in hell.
And if he is already in front of you, then he takes the view of course, so that you drive your own car there at first a few times in Klump.
Of course - you just want to make the game more exciting and exciting but this intention is so clear that it quickly gives you the joy of the game away.
And that's a pity, because despite the simpler driving model, the game is quite entertaining and sometimes so action-packed that you almost don't know where your head is.
And in principle it doesn't matter what is "guilty" about it - the concept with fifty unique routes, the arrangement of the races in a way that no boredom can arise, or something completely different...
An unusual idea is also the change of car during the race.
One must not overlook the gas stations along the route, because it is here that one can change the car, although in most cases the car is sufficient that one has just.
The cars are divided into three categories.
The sports cars are well suited for the urban areas, the strong American limousines for the straight highways and exotic super sports cars for the technical rides, for example on the serpentines in the mountains.
Hand in hand with the mode of the game history also goes the task mode (challenges) - i.e. the races in the individual locations that you know from the story.
Here there are not only medals, but also points of experience for the own profile, which is shared for the tasks (challenges) and the history.
In order to reach the higher driver level, various items have to be unlocked: from the car to the backgrounds for the profile.
This is simultaneously linked to the online autolog function, which compares, among other things, the results achieved with those of other players and also provides for further collective functions.
One of the other incomprehensible carvers is a situation in the last race of history.
Here you come by car into a subway tunnel (because of me), where you race long on the tracks in the dark (because of me).
On the speedometer numbers look between 150 a 200 km/h (because of me), but suddenly there comes from behind a subway and drives one uncompromisingly to scrap.
In our editorial office we will probably argue for a long time about whether this was a blackout of the game designers or whether the authors think we are so stupid.
The technical side is nothing overwhelming but at least the overall visual impression is quite appealing in most cases and even brilliant here and there.
All the more annoying is that at some exciting moments the refresh rate is slowing down and this is sometimes quite dramatic.
However, this is particularly true of accidents involving a greater number of participants, where a continuous FPS is of no use anyway.
The sound reproduction is OK and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an effort to reach as broad a scale as possible rather young audiences, a soundtrack a lá "something from everyone" was created - but who buys such a game because of the music?!
The overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run? The feelings are rather mixed.
If the game were not reduced by the totally unnecessary mistakes mentioned, we could have said with the breast tone that The Run is the best piece of NFS in recent years.
But that's how the game seems unfinished.
A great pleasure in itself, but you should be prepared to see these mistakes with the power of airport lights.
Concert of the "Students of the Velvet Revolution" with singing ensembles of the Karlsuniversität
The Festival Festa Academica now offers for the third time the combination of World Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution and this together with music experience.
In the course of the festival, the twenty specialist and university choirs introduce themselves.
The festival focuses on the two concerts that take place on 17 November.
"The Karlsuniversität has a big share in the festival."
