The court approves the transition to digital television in Mexico in 2015
The switch of analogue signals to digital signals has been one of the most important changes in the world in recent years.
The Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN) rejected the constitutional lawsuits filed by the Senate and the House of Deputies against the Presidential Decree, and by virtue of which the switch from analogue to digital signals must be brought forward from 2021 to 2015, due to a lack of eight votes required to challenge the law.
