The project for the lawsuit, prepared by the Minister Olga Sánchez Cordero, proposed that the Decree-Law be declared unconstitutional, since the regulations relating to radio and television are the responsibility of the Comisión Federal de Telecommunicaciones (Cofetel) (Federal Commission for Telecommunications in Mexico), which is why the Decree-Law would be contrary to the hierarchical principles and the law.
Only Zaldívar, Jorge Mario Pardo, Margarita Luna and Sánchez Cordero voted for the project.
With this argument, both the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies filed constitutional complaints against the Legislative Decree. Upon acceptance of the lawsuits, Minister Sánchez Cordero no longer applied the Legislative Decree and ceased all activities for the establishment of digital transmission.
