Fujimori returned to the hospital for medical examinations
Former President Alberto Fujimori was admitted to a public hospital on Tuesday to investigate the muscle loss of his legs, informed his family doctor.
The 72-year-old Fujimori, who is serving 25 years in prison for violation of human rights during his reign (1990-2000), has several diseases, including tongue cancer, which operates four times and is under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, Congressman and his personal physician, told television that Fujimori would be examined for three days in the Peruvian hospital Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas to determine the cause of his pain and muscle loss in the lower limbs.
Aguinaga commented that in his opinion Fujimori could be pardoned for humanitarian reasons. Nevertheless, he did not wish this because he thought he was innocent.
He has been operated on four times with tongue cancer and has lost 18 kilos of weight. In addition, the doctor listed other diseases such as severe erosive gastritis, a cyst in the pancreas, kidney stones, hypertension and blood circulation problems in the legs.
Fujimori has been in the Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía Detention Centre since September 2007.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the murder of 25 people by the Peruvian army's death squad, which was secretly active during his reign.
Mujica travels to Mexico to strengthen political relations
An official delegation led by Uruguayan President José Mujica and consisting of several ministers and entrepreneurs will start their visit to Mexico on Tuesday to expand trade between the two countries and discuss regional political issues.
Mujica will meet his Mexican counterpart Felipe Calderón next Wednesday. According to the Uruguayan president, this will be the highlight of his booked schedule with politicians, businessmen and a meeting with the collective of Uruguayans living in Mexico.
The meeting of both presidents in the city of Guadalajara "is appropriate for the exchange of information on all policy areas between the two countries", announced the presidency of the South American country on its website.
According to local media, Mujica is looking for Calderón's support for the incident with France when French head of government Nicolas Sarkozy put the South American country on a list of tax havens at the G20 summit in Cannes, France.
In his discourse, Sarkozy threatened to exclude from the international community those countries that still exist as tax havens. This declaration was rejected by Uruguay and prompted a request from his ambassador to the European country.
Mexico has been chairing the G20 since November, a group of the most powerful emerging and industrialised countries in the world. Since January of this year, there has been an agreement on the exchange of tax information to avoid double taxation with the South American country.
In recent years, the Government of Uruguay has sought to speed up the implementation of tax information exchange agreements in order to be removed from the "grey list" of the Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), which includes countries that have not adopted all international standards for tax cooperation.
At the business level, there has been a free trade agreement between Mexico and Uruguay since 2004, which has contributed to a growing exchange of goods between the two countries.
The purrbeared installer enters the third dimension with "Super Mario 3D Land"
Super Mario has fought tirelessly for 25 years for the rescue of Princess Peach from the claws of the evil Bowser, but never in three dimensions: in "Super Mario 3D Land" he fights for the love of the girl in stereo technology.
The game that comes to the store counters around the world this month has been tailored from the very beginning to the characteristics of the Nintende 3DS portable console, which can be played three-dimensionally without any special glasses.
"Mario is the figure who has to say how the stereoscopy works without glasses," assured Omar Álvarez, the responsible for the Nintendo-specialized press in Spain at the presentation of the video game in Madrid.
Álvarez stated that "Super Mario 3D Land" was "the first video game by Nintendo that was developed for this console from the very beginning", because up to now successful articles such as "Star Fox 64 3D" or "Zelda: Ocarine of time 3D" have been adaptations of existing titles.
Nintendo's spokesman pointed out that although it was three-dimensional, "Super Mario 3D Land" was a "affordable" video game that allowed a fast, fluid game.
Álvarez confirmed that "Super Mario 3D Land" contained two games in one: The first part is "light" to capture the less tasted users.
After that, the experts can turn a "second round" over the different levels of games, which are becoming increasingly difficult.
In addition, users can choose in real time between an "aggressive D" or one that only affects the depth of the action. However, in order to overcome the obstacles without being the victim of the "optical effects", it is always necessary to play three-dimensionally.
This Super Marios trip into the three-dimensional world also means the return of the figure to a portable console, which has not been the case since 2005.
With this video game Nintendo winks to the fans of the Saga and repeats the recipe for success of the last editions: The purr-bearded installer has to overcome risk-picked platforms to free Princess Peach.
However, the player encounters news in the movements, the environment, disguises and enemies - and a "playable" Luigi.
Colom guarantees delivery of Portillos to the United States
The President of Guatemala, Álvaro Colom, announced this Tuesday that he would allow the extradition of former Governor Alfonso Portillo to take responsibility in the United States for the conspiracy to pay $70 million in money laundering.
Thus, the trial of the US application for extradition of Portillo ends, so that it can be brought to justice there.
In a press conference, Colom confirmed that his decision was based on the independence of the judiciary and the government, taking into account that a ruling court had already ordered extradition.
He stressed that he had not interfered in court decisions during his government and had allowed all extradition requests which he was informed of.
Besides Portillo, Sergio Ruano Marroquín is extradited for murder and serious assault, Edgar Estrada Morales and Víctor Estrada Paredes, both for drug trafficking.
Colom's action is an act of government that takes place when all judicial and constitutional authorities have been exhausted to condemn the former President of the State (2000-2004).
According to the decisions of the Fifth Criminal Court and the Constitutional Court of Guatemala, Portillo must be extradited once its legal situation in Guatemale has been clarified and its human rights guaranteed.
Portillo was acquitted in the Ministry of Defense during his reign for the embezzlement of 120 million Quetzales, which was preceded by extradition, but the minister objected and revived the case anew.
Trinijove has helped 6000 young people threatened by social exclusion
The organisation was set up to avoid the marginalisation of young people without vocational training.
The first 25 years of the Trinijove social assistance organisation have led to important results: In this quarter century, 6000 young people threatened with social exclusion were supported in order to find a way out of their difficult situation.
In addition, there are more than one hundred jobs created for this social group.
On the occasion of the anniversary, an event in the former factory buildings of Fabra i Coats, attended by more than 300 people, was held yesterday.
Trinijove was founded in 1986 in the Trinitat Vella district with the aim of helping young people with a low level of education, without work, with drug problems at risk of marginality.
Yesterday's celebration in Sant Andreu was attended by a large number of officials from institutions and institutions who have worked with the association over the past 25 years.
The participation of political representatives from different directions during election campaigns demonstrated the impartiality of the work carried out by Trinijove.
In addition to the president of the Generalitat (Parliament of the Autonomous Region of Catalonia), Artur Mas, and his predecessor Jordi Pujol participated in the celebrations of the former socialist minister of education Ernest Maragall and the former mayor and currently left-green city councillor Ricard Goma.
The large hall of Fabra i Coats was also visited by the current Catalan Minister of Social Affairs and Family, Josep Lluís Cleries, and Jaume Lanaspa, Director General of the Social Fund of La Caixa.
Mas stressed that Trinijove was born in very difficult times and that today's times are no less complicated, but he added that the work done so far is "a good foundation".
For the president of the Generalitat, Trinijove is a model that knows how to fight difficult circumstances and gives hope to people in difficulty.
"The economic crisis is nothing new for the association and the work it does," he explained.
Occupied house, where giant parties were held, was cleared
The owners had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments in the building on the street Balmes No. 51 (Barcelona).
The twelve squatters left the building yesterday afternoon without resisting.
Everything points out that the nightmares of the neighbors of House No. 51 on the street Balmes have come to an end.
Twelve people left yesterday at noon voluntarily the building that they held illegally occupied and in which they had organized huge festivals that had driven the neighborhood to despair. The evacuation took place on a judicial order without police intervention.
After clearing, the door lock was replaced to avoid a similar situation.
"From now on, access will be controlled," the house manager confirmed.
The squatters, who had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments of the building - the others were inhabited - took the entire electrical system and part of the water supply with them. In addition, they had painted the walls and left behind all kinds of garbage, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
On the three lower floors huge parties were celebrated, which lasted up to two days and drove the tenants to despair.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which also suffered damage.
Her owner, Maria Pantinate, explained to Europa Press that her business had declined by 80% since the start of the household occupation.
The owner of the discotheque pointed out that the squatters made their unfair competition, because they sold the drinks at three euros, while in the discotheque they cost 10 euros.
In addition, the owner of the leisure place had been reported by the neighbors for disturbance of the peace, while according to their statement the noise did not come from the visitors of the disco, but from the squatters and especially from the guests of the festivals that were organized there, and which according to the angry neighbors became more and more in recent weeks.
The person responsible for the discotheque explained that the harassment was so great that it agreed with the owner of the building not to have to pay rent for the last nine months.
Guardia Urbana (urban police) also confirmed that she had received more complaints from her neighbours in the last weeks.
Last week, the president of the PP (Partido Popular - People's Party) in Barcelona's city council, Alberto Fernández Díaz, called for the building to be removed immediately and for the problems of civil coexistence to be dealt with and for the neighbourhood to come down.
He explained that only one floor of the building had been occupied before the summer, but that the squatters had penetrated into all floors of the building and almost all apartments in recent months. In some even thefts had occurred.
In this sense, he added that "it is necessary to put an end to impunity and to take action against the anti-social actions in the building."
Yesterday, another building in the Nou Barris district was cleared by the Catalan police.
At 3:30 p.m., the police approached Montral Street No. 35 after receiving a call from a neighbor who had watched four people enter the building.
The four were arrested immediately.
