Modol, like Roldán and Bayona with urban planning experience, sees the proposal as an "intellectual challenge" that carries "some dangers".
Dangers resulting from the "uncertainty that the design of a public space brings with it today" according to the experiences of the 1980s, which had their "swan singing" in the field of the forum.
The first fear is one's own limitation to what can be built.
